textRun.content: Product Enterprise: Forward Documents in Task List to Other Users
SPEC-123123 Product Enterprise - M1 - Document Forwarding ACC Model
What is the business value that the milestone will deliver

Product Automates supply chain orchestration, providing a single view into everything that touches the supply chain ecosystem. In a supply chain ecosystem, hundreds or thousands of documents can be submitted through a typical buyer/supplier relationship.  Each of these documents is processed through a workflow that can be configured to place the document in a user’s individual review workqueue. Currently reviewers can accept or reject these documents. This milestone shall change the Product API and UI to allow user forward documents from his/her review workqueue to other user’s review workqueue.
BU Authored P2 Spec - Product Mass Update Review

Lowest level of user access permission that can be granted to a user. Identifies user access to individual product function. This spec creates “Forward Documents” access function required to manage access to document forwarding.

P1 ITD 4.1 - Use existing interface to allow forward single document for a single user.
How to allow Product to forward single document for a single user?
Change API interface to support forwarding
Keep existing API interface but update it to allow document forwarding.
API is historically used across Product and changing API interface is risky.

Keeping existing interface will leave use of an API unchanged. Existing API interface supports userAction parameter that identify action being performed. Introducing a new userAction = “Forward” will allow to identify document forwarding action. API behaviour can be changed to forward document specified by trackId to the userId if “Forward” user action is specified.
Modify the new ForwardMultipleDocuments API call to support forwarding and multiple users.
P1 ITD 5.1 - Update API interface as defined by
to allow forward multiple documents for multiple users.
How to allow Product to forward multiple (one or more) documents to multiple (one or more) users?
Change API interface as defined by
to support forwarding of multiple documents to multiple users.
New API has been just introduced by recent spec so use of an API across Product is easily traceable. At the same time it is beneficial to update API interface to make its use transparent to the user.

Keeping existing interface same and parameter names unchanged will eliminate the risk of change but will cause implementation difficulties. Since the risk of the change is minimal as mentioned above this is not a preferred option.
Update API to allow Product forward documents
ForwardDocument API is updates to support forwarding of a single document to a single user.
ForwardMultipleDocuments API is updated to support forwarding of multiple (one or more) documents to multiple (one or more) users.
